{
  "id": "10062",
  "key": "GG-59",
  "fields": {
    "summary": "Develop Logic for Conditional Data Export Based on User Input",
    "description": {
      "type": "doc",
      "version": 1,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Use case:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "As a "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Product Owner",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "strong"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "I want to develop logic for conditional data export based on user input, "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "so that the exported data meets the specific requirements of different teams and systems. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "rule"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Acceptance criteria:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "GIVEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the user has provided input on the specific project and data to be exported, "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "WHEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the export operation is triggered, "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "AND",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the user's input is processed, "
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "THEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " only the selected data is fetched from Jira Cloud and transformed into JSON for export."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "rule"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Technical notes:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To achieve conditional data export based on user input, the Node JS backend will need to implement logic to collect and interpret the user's preferences. This can be achieved by creating a flexible query system that allows users to specify which types of issues, workflows, screens, and custom fields they want to include in the export."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The React Front End will need to provide a user interface that allows users to select the specific project and choose the types of data they want to export. Additionally, it should display progress as each type of data is being read and exported."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The JSON output should only include the selected data in a well-structured format as per the user's input. This may involve creating conditional logic within the data transformation process to filter out unwanted elements based on user preferences."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Collaboration with other teams should ensure that the exported JSON is clear and well-documented so that downstream teams can easily consume and utilize the data relevant to their tasks."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Sequential and secure handling of credentials and tokens must be maintained throughout this process to ensure that only authorized data is exported and that sensitive information is never exposed during any stage of the operation."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
